President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Adrianne Todman as Deputy Secretary for Housing and Urban Development (HUD). Todman is currently the CEO of the National Association of Housing and Redevelopment Officials (NAHRO). She has previously served as the Executive Director of the District of Columbia Housing Authority (DCHA) and held various positions at HUD, including managing a $500 million grant competition for the redevelopment of distressed public housing sites. Todman's extensive experience in the affordable housing industry and her background as a legislative director make her a recognized figure in the field. She is a graduate of Smith College and currently resides in Washington, D.C.